<threat_model>
## Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| RAW file → writer | Untrusted/imperfect vendor scan data crosses here; individual scans may be unreadable ("Cannot get scan event for N"). |
| temp file → STORED zip entry | Internal bytes cross from a seekable temp FileStream into a non-seekable, write-only archive stream. |

## STRIDE Threat Register

| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| T-01-01 | Denial of Service | full-facet in-RAM accumulation on multi-GB RAW (v1 OOM) | mitigate | Bounded row-group streaming to seekable temp files (Task 2); peak RSS ≈ one buffer per open facet, verified MEM-02 (Task 4). |
| T-01-02 | Tampering | non-seekable sink silently buffers whole facet (looks like streaming, isn't) | mitigate | OpenAsync asserts sink.CanSeek and throws otherwise (Task 1); NonSeekableSinkRejected test; data facets only ever target temp FileStreams. |
| T-01-03 | Tampering | mid-scan throw orphans points / reuses ordinal → facet-metadata parity break | mitigate | Per-scan all-or-nothing stage-then-commit (Task 3); ordinal advances only on full success; parity asserted in S4 test. |
| T-01-04 | Denial of Service | multi-GB temp files leaked on a mid-conversion throw | mitigate | try/finally around streaming handles + temp paths; delete all temps in finally (Task 2). |
| T-01-05 | Information Disclosure | logical output changes vs v1 (regression) | mitigate | Point layout, schemas, and footer KV unchanged; mzpeak-validate 0/0 + identical-multiset tests + full suite (Tasks 2,4). |
</threat_model>

