   217	<threat_model>
   218	## Trust Boundaries
   219	
   220	| Boundary | Description |
   221	|----------|-------------|
   222	| RAW file → writer | Untrusted/imperfect vendor scan data crosses here; individual scans may be unreadable ("Cannot get scan event for N"). |
   223	| temp file → STORED zip entry | Internal bytes cross from a seekable temp FileStream into a non-seekable, write-only archive stream. |
   224	
   225	## STRIDE Threat Register
   226	
   227	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   228	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   229	| T-01-01 | Denial of Service | full-facet in-RAM accumulation on multi-GB RAW (v1 OOM) | mitigate | Bounded row-group streaming to seekable temp files (Task 2); peak RSS ≈ one buffer per open facet, verified MEM-02 (Task 4). |
   230	| T-01-02 | Tampering | non-seekable sink silently buffers whole facet (looks like streaming, isn't) | mitigate | OpenAsync asserts sink.CanSeek and throws otherwise (Task 1); NonSeekableSinkRejected test; data facets only ever target temp FileStreams. |
   231	| T-01-03 | Tampering | mid-scan throw orphans points / reuses ordinal → facet-metadata parity break | mitigate | Per-scan all-or-nothing stage-then-commit (Task 3); ordinal advances only on full success; parity asserted in S4 test. |
   232	| T-01-04 | Denial of Service | multi-GB temp files leaked on a mid-conversion throw | mitigate | try/finally around streaming handles + temp paths; delete all temps in finally (Task 2). |
   233	| T-01-05 | Information Disclosure | logical output changes vs v1 (regression) | mitigate | Point layout, schemas, and footer KV unchanged; mzpeak-validate 0/0 + identical-multiset tests + full suite (Tasks 2,4). |
   234	</threat_model>
   235	
   236	<verification>
   237	- Full NUnit suite green native arm64 (pre-existing tests + new), DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD prefix.
   238	- small.RAW: mzpeak-validate 0/0; spectrum_count == distinct spectrum_index == metadata rows; identical point/peak totals to v1.
   239	- Multi-row-group read-back identical to single-row-group (MzPeakParquetTests + MzPeakWriterTests).
   240	- Non-seekable sink rejected (guard test).
   241	- S4_5foldGHRP.raw converts to completion, scan #25081 skipped + counted, archive valid, parity + dense ordinals.
   242	- 70JG_02.raw (954 MB) converts + validates 0/0 under bounded peak RSS (recorded); Astral 8.4 GB attempted (--quick acceptable), outcome recorded.
   243	</verification>
   244	
   245	<success_criteria>
   246	- MEM-01: writer flushes Parquet in bounded row groups (cap 1,048,576 rows); peak memory independent of point count.
   247	- MEM-02: 954 MB Orbitrap converts without OOM and validates 0/0; peak RSS recorded; Astral stretch attempted.
   248	- MEM-03: STORED-zip assembly streams temp-file bytes via 64 KB bounded CopyTo — no whole-facet/whole-archive in memory.
   249	- ROB-01: a single bad scan is logged + ParseInput.NewError()-counted + skipped; conversion continues; archive never aborted.
   250	- ROB-02: skipped scans leave dense ordinals and facet/metadata parity intact (skipped scan absent from all facets).
   251	- No v1 regression: point layout unchanged, byte-semantically identical logical output, validator 0/0, full suite green.
   252	
   253	## Definition of Done → Requirement mapping
   254	| Requirement | Satisfied by | Gate |
   255	|-------------|--------------|------|
   256	| MEM-01 | Task 1 (streaming API) + Task 2 (bounded row-group data facets, RowGroupRowCap) | multi-row-group read-back test; bounded buffers |
   257	| MEM-02 | Task 4 (70JG_02.raw under /usr/bin/time -l, validates) | recorded peak RSS + validate 0/0 |
   258	| MEM-03 | Task 2 (temp file → 64 KB CopyTo → STORED entry → delete) | AddStoredFromFile; no whole-facet byte[] for data |
   259	| ROB-01 | Task 3 (stage-then-commit; Log.Error + NewError + continue) | S4 conversion completes, error counted |
   260	| ROB-02 | Task 3 (ordinal commits only on success) | S4 parity: distinct spectrum_index == metadata rows, dense ordinals |
   261	</success_criteria>
   262	
   263	<risks>
   264	- **Primary: streaming refactor regressing v1 conformance.** The move from full-facet accumulation to incremental row groups must preserve index/multiset/footer-KV invariants. Mitigation: schemas, point layout, and footer KV strings are reused verbatim; identical-multiset + parity + full-suite tests gate every change (Tasks 2,4).
   265	- **The silent-buffer trap.** A non-seekable sink (e.g. accidentally handing the zip-entry stream to ParquetWriter) buffers the whole facet in RAM with no error — invisible RSS regression. Mitigation: OpenAsync asserts CanSeek; data facets only ever target temp FileStreams; NonSeekableSinkRejected test (Task 1); warning sign = RSS scaling with file size despite "streaming" / zero temp files on disk (Task 4 RSS measurement catches it).
   266	- **Buffer sizing with three open facets (RESEARCH A2).** 3 × 1M-row buffers ≈ tens of MB; if too large, lower RowGroupRowCap (one-line const). Caught at Task 4 measurement.
   267	- **Corpus availability.** MEM-02 / ROB gates depend on the large files being present; verified present today (954 MB, 418 MB, 8.4 GB). The robustness NUnit test self-ignores off-corpus so the suite stays green elsewhere.
   268	- **Exact S4 throw line unconfirmed (RESEARCH A1).** The all-or-nothing staging is correct whether the throw is before or after the old append; optionally log the first occurrence's stack to confirm. Low risk.
   269	</risks>
